  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/707",
  "title": "Customize hits template",
  "body": "Hi,\n\nThe current hits widgets only allows to provide a template per hit, I would like to provide a global template so that I can add any HTML attribute I need.\n\nIt could make sense to make it overridable with something like:\n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.hits({\n   container: '#hits',\n   templates: {\n        empty: '<div class=\"text-center\">No results found matching <strong>{{query}}</strong>.</div>',\n        items: '<div class=\"hits\">{{#hits}}Hello {{hit.name}}{{/hits}}</div>'\n   }\n});\n```\n\nWhat do you think about it?\n",
